contentheadline.headline: Islamic Action Organization In Iraq – Central Command

contentrichtext.text: {{Politics of Iraq}} The '''Islamic Action Organization In Iraq – Central Command''' is one of the electoral coalitions that participated in the January 30, 2005 [[Iraqi parliamentary election, January 2005|National Assembly legislative election]] in [[Iraq]]. It is linked with the [[Islamic Action Organization]] which ran as a part of the [[United Iraqi Alliance]]. In the 2005 election, the party received 43,205 votes, or 0.51% of the ballot, earning them two seats in the National Assembly. The list's leader was given as [[Ala Humud Salih al Tamah]]. In the December 2005 elections, they won no seats. ==References== {{Empty section|date=July 2010}} ==External links== {{DEFAULTSORT:Islamic Action Organization In Iraq - Central Command}} [[Category:Political parties in Iraq]] {{Iraq-stub}}
